// Ultrasonic Sensor Connections with Raspberry Pi 


▪️ Device Needs : 

1) Raspberry Pi
2) Ultrasonic sensor (HC-SR04)
3) Jumper Wires (4) 


▪️ Connect the Peripherals : (raspberry pi)

1) Attach a keyboard and mouse to the Raspberry Pi USB 2.
2) Attach a monitor to the Raspberry Pi HDMI Port.
3) Connect a Raspberry Pi Power Supply pin to the Raspberry Pi USB -C.


▪️ Jumper Wire Connection Between :

Ultrasonic - Raspberry Pi
1) VCC - pin 4 (5v)
2) Echo - pin 38 (GPIO 20)
3) Trig - pin 40 (GPIO 21)
4) GND - pin 6 (ground) 

